│ "The issue is an incorrect transformation in GVN where an instruction is replaced by a     │
│ congruent one with incompatible `!range` metadata. This leads to `poison` values being     │
│ introduced incorrectly.\n\n**1. Understanding the Issue:**\nGVN replaces `%ctpop2` with    │
│ `%ctpop1` because they are congruent `llvm.ctpop.i32(%x)` calls. However, `%ctpop1` has    │
│ `range(1, 32)` and `%ctpop2` has `range(0, 33)`. When `%x` is 0, `%ctpop` is 0. The        │
│ original code is correct because 0 is in `[0, 33)`. The transformed code is incorrect      │
│ because 0 is not in `[1, 32)`, making the value `poison`.\n\n**2. Analyzing `opt`'s        │
│ Log:**\nThe log `GVN removed: %ctpop2 = ...` confirms that GVN performs the problematic    │
│ replacement.\n\n**3. Root Cause Analysis:**\nThe root cause is that GVN's instruction      │
│ comparison logic for CSE does not account for `!range` metadata. When replacing an         │
│ instruction `I` with a value `V`, it doesn't check if the metadata is compatible. The      │
│ replacement is only safe if the range of `V` contains the range of `I`. If `V` has a       │
│ narrower range, it can invalidate uses of `I` that relied on the wider range.\n\n**4.      │
│ Proposed Edit Point(s):**\nThe fix is to add a check in `GVN::processInstruction` before   │
│ replacing an instruction. This check will compare the `!range` metadata of the instruction │
│ to be replaced (`I`) and the replacement value (`V`). The replacement will be aborted if   │
│ both have `!range` metadata and the range of `V` does not contain the range of             │
│ `I`.\n\n```cpp\n          // Check for range metadata.\n          if                       │
│ (I->hasMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range) &&\n                                                │
│ V->hasMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range)) {\n            ConstantRange RangeI =               │
│ I->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range)\n                                                    │
│ ->getOperand(0)\n                                       .get()\n                           │
│ ->getConstantRange();\n            ConstantRange RangeV =                                  │
│ V->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range)\n                                                    │
│ ->getOperand(0)\n                                       .get()\n                           │
│ ->getConstantRange();\n            if (!RangeV.contains(RangeI))\n                         │
│ continue;\n          }\n```\nThis code should be inserted at line 2742 in                  │
│ `llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/GVN.cpp`, just before the call to                              │
│ `patchAndReplaceAllUsesWith`.\n\n**5. Conclusion:**\nThis patch will make GVN aware of     │
│ `!range` metadata, preventing it from making replacements that would incorrectly narrow    │
│ the promised range of a value. This will fix the reported miscompilation and make GVN      │
│ safer in the presence of range metadata."})                                                │
